{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Chandler Moisen","author":"Chandler Moisen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"729bf62c-247e-53c3-ab27-ca19912e40ec","excerpt":"I have relied on Pigeon to navigate the mess that is the NYC MTA for nearly a year.You can think of Pigeon as the New York City Subway’s Waze. Sprouting from an…","html":"<p>I have relied on <a href=\"https://pigeon.area120.com/\">Pigeon</a> to navigate the mess that is the NYC MTA for nearly a year.</p>\n<p>You can think of Pigeon as the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/31/17414330/google-area-120-pigeon-nyc-subway-app\">New York City Subway’s Waze</a>. Sprouting from an incubator within Google, Pigeon crowdsources </p>\n<p>While I could go on at length about Pigeon’s UI and features, something they recently did struck me as interesting:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4ae991f81ab558e117bcf9a0c44d640f/135ae/oops-pigeon.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 300px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 177.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"pigeon transit app error\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4ae991f81ab558e117bcf9a0c44d640f/135ae/oops-pigeon.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4ae991f81ab558e117bcf9a0c44d640f/cf440/oops-pigeon.png 148w,\n/static/4ae991f81ab558e117bcf9a0c44d640f/d2d38/oops-pigeon.png 295w,\n/static/4ae991f81ab558e117bcf9a0c44d640f/135ae/oops-pigeon.png 300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>Pigeon sent me a notification that they had messed up!</p>\n<p>Perhaps I have been living under a rock, but I do not see this pattern all to often.</p>\n<p>Firms do notify of credit card, PII breaches, product safety recalls.</p>\n<p>Something so insignificant: not receiving notifications was owned.</p>\n<p>Product team took a gamble: notify and look stupid or</p>\n<p>Makes me respect the team that built it more.</p>\n<p>Curious if this pattern exists elsewhere!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Own Your Mistakes","date":"June 22, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/own-your-mistakes/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/omny-release-and-risks/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"OMNY Release, Risks, and UX Considerations"}},"next":null}}